<TEXT>
Canadian Charitable Organizations - Dennis and Phyllis Washington Foundation Canadian Charitable Organizations The Dennis & Phyllis Washington Foundation accepts applications from Canadian organizations on an invitational basis. 
To be invited to apply for a grant, each Canadian organization must first send a letter of inquiry (LOI) to the Foundation. 
Please know that if your program falls within any of the Ineligible Categories , your request will not be considered. 
If your organization and project/program meet with the Foundation’s mission and areas of focus, you may send a letter of inquiry to the Foundation. 
If your organization is granted an invitation to submit the online application and accompanying foreign equivalency documents, you will be notified within 90 days of receipt of your letter of inquiry. 
LOI guidelines Letters should be no more than two pages. 
Supplemental attachments will not be considered. 
Letters should contain: Description of Applying Organization Summary-level project budget (including a description of what Foundation funds would be used for specifically, if approved) Submit LOIs to: Dennis & Phyllis Washington Foundation Attn: Mike Halligan PO Box 16630 Missoula, MT 59808 Or via email to info@dpwfoundation.org How to Apply If your organization qualifies, based on the Grant Guidelines, and you are interested in applying for a grant, you must complete the online application process. 
Organizations must meet certain criteria to be considered for a Washington Foundation grant. 
The Eligibility Review is the first step in the application process. 
By completing the form, we are better able to assess your organization's request. 
When grant funds have been expended, or no later than one year after receipt of the grant, please file the Grant Report which can be found by logging into your account. 
The Dennis & Phyllis Washington Foundation P.O. Box 16630 Missoula, MT 59808 Contact Us Connect With Us
</TEXT>
</DOC>

